<title>FRANCE: French govt should keep Air France stake - minister.</title>
<headline>French govt should keep Air France stake - minister.</headline>
<dateline>PARIS 1997-03-28</dateline>
<text>
<p>The French government should keep a stake in flag carrier Air France after its privatisation, Anne-Marie Idrac, a junior transport minister, said on Friday.</p>
<p>&quot;Personally, I think the state should keep a holding in Air France's capital, taking into account the strategic nature of its business,&quot; Idrac said in an interview with the newspaper Le Monde.</p>
<p>Air France is slated for privatisation but no date has been set. Chairman Christian Blanc said in January he wanted to hold the sale later this year or early in 1998, with employees owning between 20 to 30 percent of the shares.</p>
